comments.body:
Great, thanks for the clarifications.

> If we had some sort of common code project for containers/ projects, I'd vote to stick these annotations there, outside of CRI-O or Libpod. Doesn't seem to fit in Image or Storage, though.

@rhatdan @mheon I would prefer to have it in something like this dedicated, which would make the transition for cri-o a bit easier. Now we would have to wait for the next libpod version before touching cri-o. Beside this, some architectural adaptions (like mentioned in the example in #2791) would be needed for libpod as well to fit into cri-o. On the other side I must say handling another dependency more makes it not less complex.
